02/Nov/18 1:02 PM;gudkov;[~burdettadam] Wallet access is handle based. Opening and closing are performed only by application by getting handle. As a result application always knows open/close status and you don’t need dedicated api for this. 

Checking for existence can be done with create method as it returns corresponded error code. Very important is that libindy isn’t responsible for global wallets discovery. If you need to get list of existing wallets you need to store this list inside of application. 

If you see any use cases that can’t be achieved by the current API let’s create a new user story and we will analyze it. ;;;

